reviews.text:
2018-12-18 
➡️ I am quite conservative, so let's start with 4⭐ to begin with.

Had team lunch this week:
😊 Good n quiet place. Pretty nice n clean decor.

😏 No set, so in the end the cost may higher than expected/anticipated.

😊 The beef burger is good. Others may said "dry" / "not juicy" .. but maybe because of health conscious prep thus less oily / less fatty.

😏 But on the other hand, there's no other replacement for fries. I think if they can offer salad or coleslaw or mashed potatoes as alternative, it can be better n more relevant.

We asked for chicken and they cooked rubber bands with the chicken. We complained to the chef and he didn't apologize. Instead he said "those rubber bands are healthy. You don't know because you are Asian." WORST. PLACE. EVER.
DO NOT RECOMMEND AT ALL unless you like the taste of rubber bands and getting rude racist comments from chefs
waitress can't do the math, literally. Check your bill carefully before you pay!

Nice place, one of the best chicken in HK. The French chef really knows what he is doing and he's got a lot of experience working for top restaurants. The place is cosy. You can also buy fresh premium meat to cook at home. When it comes to beef they give real portions like 250g steak. It's by far the best quality food you can find in Tung Chung or even Lantau!

Burger ok..
-2 stars for Serving of chips.. minimal in takeaway order.. 5 chips

reviews.text: nic pleace
Very good club house for kids to play.

Nice and clean. Nice seaview.
Rent on the E Flat is 28,000 HKD at the moment. It used to be 20,000 when it first opened. 

Take 37M which takes you to the Tung Chung MTR Station.
One of the posch appartment complexes in the vicinity with all basic amenities. The free shuttle bus facility is not that useful because of its less frequency from the nearby MTR station
Very good apartments. Condo could be a lot better (deserves an inside good restaurant just like the one in Century Link).
